.Dd July 10, 2026
.Dt TTycITY 6
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm ttycity
.Nd terminal port of Micropolis (SimCity Classic)
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar options
.Op Ar cityfile
.Op Ar seed
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is an ncurses-based port of
.Micropolis Activity
(the open-source version of SimCity Classic by Maxis).
The original simulation engine is preserved; the X11/Tk front end is replaced
with a terminal UI that works in any modern terminal emulator.
.Pp
All game assets (scenarios, example cities) are compiled into the binary.
No external resource files are needed at runtime.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl gfx Ar mode
Select the tile-graphics rendering mode.
Without
.Fl gfx ,
the mode is auto-detected from the
.Ev TERM
and locale environment variables.
Available modes:
.Bl -tag -width "unicode" -compact
.It Cm color
1 column per tile, plain ASCII with ACS line-drawing and 8 colors.
Works on any curses implementation.
This is the default mode.
.It Cm unicode
2 columns per tile, UTF-8: emoji buildings, box-drawing roads and rails,
quadrant-block density fills, braille terrain textures.
Requires a UTF-8 locale and a wide-capable curses library.
.It Cm ascii
1 column per tile, strict 7-bit ASCII, monochrome.
No color is emitted anywhere; only bold and reverse video are used
(the VT100-era look).
.It Cm acs
1 column per tile, monochrome like
.Cm ascii
but with real ACS box-drawing for roads, rails, and power lines.
.It Cm aa
2 columns per tile, aalib dithered shading in color.
Optional; only available when built with
.Ic make aalib .
.El
.Pp
Aliases:
.Cm default
and
.Cm standard
are synonyms for
.Cm color ;
.Cm emoji
for
.Cm unicode ;
.Cm vt100 ,
.Cm mono ,
.Cm bw ,
and
.Cm 7bit
for
.Cm ascii ;
.Cm aalib
and
.Cm aa-lib
for
.Cm aa .
.Pp
Use
.Fl gfx help
or
.Fl gfx list
to show all modes and their availability.
.It Fl theme Ar name
Set the land background color theme.
Available themes:
.Bl -tag -width "grass" -compact
.It Cm tan
Yellow-brown ground (default).
.It Cm grass
Green ground.
.It Cm dark
Black ground.
.El
.It Fl shot Ar path
Headless screenshot mode: advance
.Ar frames
iterations, render the screen to
.Ar path
as plain text, and exit.
Implies no interactive session.
.It Fl frames Ar N
Number of simulation frames to advance in
.Fl shot
mode.
Defaults to 60.
.It Fl gfx Ar help
.It Fl gfx Ar list
Print the list of available graphics modes and exit.
.El
.Pp
If an argument ends in
.Pa .cty
or
.Pa .scn ,
it is loaded as a city or scenario file.
Otherwise, if the argument is a bare integer, it is used as the random seed
for generating a new city.
.Sh CONTROLS
.Ss Keyboard
.Bl -tag -width "space" -compact
.It Ic arrow keys , hjkl
Move the cursor.
.It Ic Shift+letter
Pick a tool (see
.Sx TOOLS
below).
.It Ic Enter , x
Build with the current tool at the cursor.
.It Ic m
Cycle the overview minimap and overlays.
.It Ic u
Open the graphics-mode picker.
.It Ic space
Pause / unpause the simulation.
.It Ic 0 Ns , Ns Ic 1 Ns , Ns Ic 2 Ns , Ns Ic 3
Set simulation speed: 0 = pause, 1 = slow, 2 = medium, 3 = fast.
.It Ic Esc , F10
Open the menu bar.
.It Ic g
Generate a new random city.
.It Ic q
Quit.
.It Ic \`
Take a screenshot to
.Pa /tmp/ttycity_shot.txt .
.It Ic Tab , ]
Select the next tool.
.It Ic [
Select the previous tool.
.El
.Ss Mouse
If ncurses mouse support is available:
.Bl -tag -width "right-drag" -compact
.It Ic left click
Build with the current tool, select a tool on the palette, jump
the minimap, or activate a menu item.
.It Ic right drag
Pan the map view.
.It Ic wheel
Scroll the cursor up or down.
.It Ic right click (no drag)
Dismiss popups.
.El
.Pp
The terminal must support mouse reporting; most modern emulators do.
.Ss Menu Bar
The menu bar appears at the top of the screen.
It contains the following menus:
.Bl -tag -width Disasters -compact
.It Ic File
New City, Load Built-in, Load from Disk, Save City, Save As, Quit.
.It Ic Options
Auto Budget, Auto Bulldoze, Auto Goto, Disasters, Sound, Animation,
Messages, Notices, Land Color, Graphics mode picker.
.It Ic Disasters
Monster, Fire, Flood, Tornado, Earthquake, Meltdown.
.It Ic Speed
Pause, Slow, Medium, Fast.
.It Ic Views
Budget, Evaluation, Graph, Map/Overlay.
.El
.Pp
Navigate with arrow keys or hjkl; Enter selects; Esc closes.
.Sh TOOLS
Tools are selected with uppercase letters or by cycling with Tab.
The tool palette is shown on the left side of the screen.
.Pp
The following tools are available:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "CoalPower" -compact -offset indent
.It Ic R
Residential zone
.It Ic C
Commercial zone
.It Ic I
Industrial zone
.It Ic F
Fire department
.It Ic Q
Query (inspect a zone)
.It Ic P
Police department
.It Ic W
Power line (wire)
.It Ic B
Bulldozer
.It Ic K
Park / trees
.It Ic L
Rail
.It Ic O
Road
.It Ic S
Stadium
.It Ic E
Seaport
.It Ic G
Coal power plant
.It Ic N
Nuclear power plant
.It Ic A
Airport
.El
.Pp
Each tool has a build cost; insufficient funds are reported in the status line.
Zones must be placed on cleared (bulldozed) land.
.Sh SCREEN LAYOUT
The screen is divided into:
.Bl -tag -width "minimap" -compact
.It Em toolbar
Left column: tool palette with colored buttons.
.It Em editor
Center: the main map viewport (scrollable).
.It Em minimap
Right panel (toggle with
.Ic m ) :
overview map with optional overlays (pollution, crime, density, land value,
power).
On narrow terminals the minimap overlays the editor instead.
.It Em status bar
Bottom line: transient messages, scrolling advisories, or a quick-reference
help line.
.It Em left panel
Between the toolbar and the editor: city name, date, funds, population,
score, and RCI demand bars.
.El
.Sh BUILT-IN CITIES
Several example cities are bundled into the binary.
Load them from
.Ic File > Load Built-in
or by passing their name on the command line.
Available cities include:
bruce, about, badnews, bluebird, deadwood, finnigan, freds,
happisle, haight, joffburg, kobe, kowloon, kyoto, kamakura,
linecity, med_isle, neatmap, ndulls, radial, senri, southpac,
splats, wetcity, yokohama.
.Sh SCENARIOS
The following scenarios are available from
.Ic File > New Game :
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "Rio de Janeiro" -compact
.It Dullsville
A small, lifeless town (1900).
.It San Francisco
Earthquake (1906).
.It Hamburg
Fire bombing (1944).
.It Bern
Chemical spill (1965).
.It Tokyo
Monster attack (1957).
.It Detroit
Crime wave (1972).
.It Boston
Nuclear meltdown (2010).
.It Rio de Janeiro
Tornado (2047).
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width SIMHOME -compact
.It Ev SIMHOME
Override the default home directory for the city browser's starting folder.
If unset, the binary probes several locations for a
.Pa cities/
subdirectory.
.It Ev TERM
Used for auto-detection of graphics mode and color capabilities.
.It Ev LC_ALL , Ev LC_CTYPE , Ev LANG
Checked for UTF-8 locale to auto-select the unicode graphics mode.
.It Ev COLORTERM
If set to
.Ev truecolor
or
.Ev 24bit ,
unicode mode is auto-selected (if a UTF-8 locale is also available).
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width /usr/local/share/ttycity/cities -compact
.It Pa /usr/local/share/ttycity/cities
Default installed location for the built-in city files.
.It Pa /tmp/ttycity_shot.txt
Screenshot output from the
.Ic \`
key.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Start with a new random city:
.Pp
.Dl $ ttycity
.Pp
Load a saved city file:
.Pp
.Dl $ ttycity mycity.cty
.Pp
Start with emoji graphics and a grass theme:
.Pp
.Dl $ ttycity -gfx unicode -theme grass
.Pp
Force the 7-bit monochrome mode for a VT100:
.Pp
.Dl $ ttycity -gfx ascii
.Pp
Take a headless screenshot after 120 frames:
.Pp
.Dl $ ttycity -shot /tmp/city.txt -frames 120
.Pp
Generate a city from a fixed seed:
.Pp
.Dl $ ttycity 42
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr ncurses 3
.Sh HISTORY
.Nm
is a port of
.Micropolis Activity ,
which was originally released by Maxis, later released for Unix in 1990,
and finally open-sourced by Electronic Arts Inc. for the One Laptop Per
Child program.
The simulation engine was written by Will Wright.
The ncurses front end preserves the original game logic and adds a
terminal-native interface.
